<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-297-876  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 297 876.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 2 1990 n361 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Factory looks to cut costs. (Computer Factory Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hedlund, Kristen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Computer Factory Inc will introduce some internalorganizational changes it hopes will help revamp the firm's coststructure.andP;  The main element of the plan concerns reducing thenumber of direct sale locations from 68 locations to 21.andP;  Theremaining locations will be solely retail outlets.andP;  Currently all68 locations have their own out-bound-sales force, but under theplan the 21 locations will become high-level support centers.andP;  Themove is not expected to eliminate any jobs.andP;  The move is expectedto improve profit margins through increased efficiency.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Factory Inc. (management).andO;Topic:     Cost ReductionFinancial AnalysisOrganization StructureComputer RetailingOutside Sales.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>